# Global Git excludes (core.excludesfile). Applies to every repo on this machine.

# Keep Claude Code's local settings (permissions, etc.) out of commits
**/.claude/settings.local.json

# NOTE: .gitignore and .editorconfig are deliberately NOT excluded here — they are
# meant to be committed and shared per-repo (a global exclude only applies on this
# machine, so the rule wouldn't travel to clones/collaborators/CI anyway). Project
# ignores belong in a committed .gitignore; "just this clone" ignores go in
# .git/info/exclude. Only put truly never-commit-anywhere noise in this file.

